Class MovieRental

java.lang.Object
classes.MovieRental
All Implemented Interfaces:
Payment
public class MovieRental extends Object implements Payment
Represents a movie rental transaction and implements Payment to compute fees. Keeps numeric customer/movie ids (internal) and rental dates.

    • MovieRental

      public MovieRental(int customerID, String membership, int movieID, LocalDate beginDate, LocalDate returnDate, boolean rentable)
      Create a MovieRental instance.
      Parameters:
      customerID - internal numeric customer id
      membership - membership type string (e.g. "Student" or "Regular")
      movieID - internal numeric movie id
      beginDate - rental begin date
      returnDate - scheduled return date (may be null)
      rentable - true when movie is available (returned), false when rented

    • calculate

      public double calculate()
      Calculate rental fee based on membership and nights rented. Students: STUDENT_FEE for first week then $1 per extra night. External members: EXTERNAL_MEMBER_FEE for first week then $2 per extra night.
      Specified by:
      calculate in interface Payment
      Returns:
      total fee as double
